<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 18 Apr 2026 01:16:59 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>科学家仍然不知道大峡谷是如何或何时形成的。新研究可能暗示其古老起源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-still-dont-know-how-or-when-the-grand-canyon-formed-new-research-may-hint-at-its-ancient-origins-180988570/</link><description>研究人员表示，大约 660 万年前，古老的科罗拉多河在亚利桑那州北部形成了一个古老的湖泊，该湖泊向西溢出，最终形成了大峡谷</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 19:11:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-still-dont-know-how-or-when-the-grand-canyon-formed-new-research-may-hint-at-its-ancient-origins-180988570/</guid></item><item><title>伦敦莎士比亚故居已消失在历史之中。一位学者在档案馆中发现了一张地图，显示了其确切位置</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/shakespeares-house-in-london-was-lost-to-history-a-scholar-discovered-a-map-in-the-archives-that-revealed-its-exact-location-180988566/</link><description>这位诗人在 1616 年去世前三年购买了这处房产。他是否希望在这座他创作最著名戏剧的城市度过更多的时光？</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 18:46:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/shakespeares-house-in-london-was-lost-to-history-a-scholar-discovered-a-map-in-the-archives-that-revealed-its-exact-location-180988566/</guid></item><item><title>83 年前，第一次 LSD 旅行实际上是骑自行车。迷幻迷们每年 4 月 19 日都会庆祝这个节日</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-first-lsd-trip-was-a-literal-bicycle-ride-83-years-ago-fans-of-the-psychedelic-celebrate-the-occasion-every-april-19-180988564/</link><description>1943年，瑞士的一位化学家合成了一种改变意识的药物。他的发现改变了医学、精神病学和生物学的研究，并成为反主流文化运动的核心组成部分</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:56:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-first-lsd-trip-was-a-literal-bicycle-ride-83-years-ago-fans-of-the-psychedelic-celebrate-the-occasion-every-april-19-180988564/</guid></item><item><title>数百名西班牙定居者死于“饥荒港”。这枚新发现的银币揭示了 400 年前这个注定要灭亡的殖民地的建立地点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hundreds-of-spanish-settlers-died-at-the-port-of-famine-this-newly-discovered-silver-coin-reveals-where-the-doomed-colony-was-founded-400-years-ago-180988519/</link><description>费利佩国王城 (Ciudad del Rey Don Felipe) 于 1584 年在智利麦哲伦海峡北岸建立。几年后，当一位英国航海家发现它时，幸存者所剩无几。</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:42:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hundreds-of-spanish-settlers-died-at-the-port-of-famine-this-newly-discovered-silver-coin-reveals-where-the-doomed-colony-was-founded-400-years-ago-180988519/</guid></item><item><title>绕月飞行后，阿耳忒弥斯 2 号宇航员反思这次经历的艰巨性：“我们作为国家和人类做到了这一点”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-rounding-the-moon-artemis-2-astronauts-reflect-on-the-enormity-of-the-experience-we-as-countries-and-as-humans-did-this-180988568/</link><description>在从太空返回后的第一次新闻发布会上，四名宇航员描述了自己的渺小但与地球上的人们团结在一起的感觉，并表示这次任务是全人类的成就</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 15:01:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-rounding-the-moon-artemis-2-astronauts-reflect-on-the-enormity-of-the-experience-we-as-countries-and-as-humans-did-this-180988568/</guid></item><item><title>丰富的浆果收获让这些矮胖的濒临灭绝的鹦鹉心情愉悦。现在，科学家们正在庆祝育种繁荣</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-bountiful-berry-harvest-put-these-chunky-endangered-parrots-in-the-mood-now-scientists-are-celebrating-a-breeding-bonanza-180988510/</link><description>新西兰的鸮鹦鹉已产下 256 枚蛋，其中约 100 枚已孵化，为长达数十年的保护工作提供了亮点。官方的雏鸟数量要到最小的雏鸟大约五个月大时才会得到确认</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-bountiful-berry-harvest-put-these-chunky-endangered-parrots-in-the-mood-now-scientists-are-celebrating-a-breeding-bonanza-180988510/</guid></item><item><title>为什么这座中世纪英国城堡下面埋有冷战时期的碉堡？如果发生核“世界末日”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-a-cold-war-bunker-buried-underneath-this-medieval-english-castle-in-case-of-nuclear-armageddon-180988561/</link><description>考古学家在斯卡伯勒城堡下方发现了 20 世纪冲突的遗迹，数十年后，地堡被封锁，其确切位置已被遗忘</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 19:00:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-is-a-cold-war-bunker-buried-underneath-this-medieval-english-castle-in-case-of-nuclear-armageddon-180988561/</guid></item><item><title>这些小蚂蚁在大蚂蚁身上爬行，然后把它们舔干净。科学家们不确定这种行为对他们有什么好处</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-tiny-ants-crawled-all-over-larger-ants-and-licked-them-clean-scientists-arent-sure-how-this-behavior-benefits-any-of-them-180988555/</link><description>在目睹了亚利桑那州沙漠中的相互作用后，史密森学会的一位研究人员表示，小蚂蚁会摘取美味佳肴，而大蚂蚁则会在难以到达的地方进行彻底的梳理。</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 18:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-tiny-ants-crawled-all-over-larger-ants-and-licked-them-clean-scientists-arent-sure-how-this-behavior-benefits-any-of-them-180988555/</guid></item><item><title>大型入侵啮齿动物正在加州造成严重破坏。新研究表明有人故意引入它们</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-invasive-rodents-are-wreaking-havoc-in-california-new-research-suggests-someone-deliberately-introduced-them-180988554/</link><description>基因测试显示，自 2017 年以来生活在加利福尼亚州的海狸鼠与俄勒冈州中部的海狸鼠种群关系最为密切——距离太远，这些生物无法自行迁徙</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-invasive-rodents-are-wreaking-havoc-in-california-new-research-suggests-someone-deliberately-introduced-them-180988554/</guid></item><item><title>20 世纪 90 年代，一只狗教孩子们了解莎士比亚和荷马。一部新纪录片讲述“叉骨”的故事——从他的后空翻到他的历史帽子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-1990s-a-dog-taught-kids-about-shakespeare-and-homer-a-new-documentary-tells-the-tale-of-wishbone-from-his-backflips-to-his-historical-hats-180988552/</link><description>这部电影让演员和工作人员重聚，他们看到了杰克罗素梗犬在 PBS 上将经典文学带入生活的潜力</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 15:31:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-the-1990s-a-dog-taught-kids-about-shakespeare-and-homer-a-new-documentary-tells-the-tale-of-wishbone-from-his-backflips-to-his-historical-hats-180988552/</guid></item><item><title>中世纪的文字和树木年轮帮助研究人员追踪 800 年前的太阳风暴并重建过去的太阳周期</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/medieval-writings-and-tree-rings-helped-researchers-track-a-solar-storm-from-800-years-ago-and-reconstruct-past-solar-cycles-180988546/</link><description>日本诗人藤原帝家的日记以及来自亚洲和欧洲的其他历史资料在一项新研究中发挥了关键作用</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/medieval-writings-and-tree-rings-helped-researchers-track-a-solar-storm-from-800-years-ago-and-reconstruct-past-solar-cycles-180988546/</guid></item><item><title>伊利湖的这艘运石船遭遇突如其来的暴风雨。 150 多年后，潜水员刚刚发现沉船</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-sudden-squall-doomed-this-stone-hauling-vessel-in-lake-erie-divers-just-found-the-shipwreck-more-than-150-years-later-180988557/</link><description>1868 年 9 月，一艘 125 英尺长的小船“Clough”在克利夫兰附近沉没，只有一名船员幸存并解释了发生的事情</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 13:35:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-sudden-squall-doomed-this-stone-hauling-vessel-in-lake-erie-divers-just-found-the-shipwreck-more-than-150-years-later-180988557/</guid></item><item><title>犹他州上空高耸的发光球体发出了紧急的艺术信息：大盐湖正在干涸</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-glowing-sphere-towering-over-utah-sent-an-urgent-artistic-message-the-great-salt-lake-is-drying-up-180988553/</link><description>奥拉维尔·埃利亚松的最新装置将视觉效果与音景结合起来，吸引公众对重要生态系统困境的关注</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 13:00:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-new